1. Make the rules files be owned by root:root
                               user-^ group-^

sudo chown root:root /path/to/rules/*.rules

2. Have the file permissions be 644 (rw-r--r--)
sudo chmod 644 /path/to/rules/*.rules

3. Put the rules files in /etc/udev/rules.d/
sudo mv /path/to/rules/*.rules /etc/udev/rules.d
